Remote Desktop Easy Print – Descriptive Explanation (Exam-Oriented, Easy Language)
1. Introduction
Remote Desktop Easy Print is a feature in Windows Remote Desktop Services (RDS) that allows users to print documents from a remote session to their local printer without installing printer drivers on the remote server. It simplifies printing in remote environments and makes printer redirection easy and efficient.
2. What is Remote Desktop Easy Print?
Remote Desktop Easy Print is a driver-less printing technology introduced by Microsoft. It uses the Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP) to redirect print jobs from a remote computer (server) to a user’s local printer.
👉 In simple words:
It allows you to print from a remote computer to your own local printer without needing to install printer drivers on the server.
3. How Remote Desktop Easy Print Works
The working of Easy Print can be explained step-by-step:
A user connects to a remote computer using Remote Desktop
The local printer is automatically redirected into the remote session
The user gives a print command from the remote application
The print job is processed in a universal format (XPS – XML Paper Specification)
The job is sent back through the RDP connection to the client computer
The local computer receives the job and prints it using its own printer driver
4. Key Features of Remote Desktop Easy Print
No Driver Installation Required
No need to install printer drivers on the remote server
Automatic Printer Redirection
Local printers are automatically available in the remote session
Universal Printing Format (XPS)
Uses XPS format for consistent and high-quality output
Improved Compatibility
Works with almost all printers without compatibility issues
Simplified Management
Reduces administrative effort in managing printer drivers
User-Friendly
Easy to use for both administrators and end users
5. Advantages of Remote Desktop Easy Print
Saves time by eliminating driver installation
Reduces server load and complexity
Improves security by avoiding third-party drivers on the server
Ensures consistent printing experience
Ideal for remote work and virtual environments
6. Limitations of Remote Desktop Easy Print
Requires Remote Desktop Services environment
May have limited support for advanced printer features
Depends on RDP connection quality
Works best with modern Windows systems
7. Where It Is Used
In organizations using Remote Desktop Services (RDS)
Virtual Desktop Infrastructure (VDI) environments
Work-from-home setups
Cloud-based systems where users access remote machines
